-7-OLasK5ZW4yMGFd_tEJ03ABhmeSwzStoIB_WJignYGw8XC2zh9a6pkA1Lw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test workflows**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the testing workflow and wondering if I should use `javaTest` for the JVM and then `nativeTestCompile` with the generated metadata. The tests are TCK to validate the metadata, and I’m not sure if they're using repository metadata or the generated one. Oh, and it seems like for a test project, the GraalVM native plugin with agent conditional is set up too. I’ll need to clarify that.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Wx4MIFOUrmdTQ0yyUnsMSSwq|fc_0fc034284cdea3ba0169f65564b9a081a1b3fcf035d9ef5448", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.lettuce/lettuce-core/6.2.6.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_lettuce/lettuce_core/ReflectionUtilsTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_lettuce.lettuce_core;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport io.lettuce.core.ConnectionPoint;\nimport io.lettuce.core.RedisURI;\nimport io.lettuce.core.dynamic.support.ReflectionUtils;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ReflectionUtilsTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void findsInterfaceAndClassMethodsAndInvokesClassMethod() {\n        Method interfaceMethod = ReflectionUtils.findMethod(ConnectionPoint.class, \"getHost\");\n        assertThat(interfaceMethod).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(interfaceMethod.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(ConnectionPoint.class);\n\n        Method classMethod = ReflectionUtils.findMethod(RedisURI.class, \"getHost\");\n        assertThat(classMethod).isNotNull();\n\n        RedisURI redisUri = RedisURI.Builder.redis(\"localhost\", 6379).build();\n        assertThat(ReflectionUtils.invokeMethod(classMethod, redisUri)).isEqualTo(redisUri.getHost());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void visitsDeclaredFieldsAndReadsPublicStaticField() {\n        AtomicReference<Object> value = new AtomicReference<>();\n\n        ReflectionUtils.doWithFields(RedisURI.class,\n                field -> value.set(ReflectionUtils.getField(field, null)),\n                field -> field.getName().equals(\"URI_SCHEME_REDIS\"));\n\n        assertThat(value.get()).isEqualTo(RedisURI.URI_SCHEME_REDIS);\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1797, "output": 1638, "cacheRead": 44544, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47979, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777751381224, "responseId": "resp_0fc034284cdea3ba0169f65555b93481a19497124a21330a25"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Wx4MIFOUrmdTQ0yyUnsMSSwq|fc_0fc034284cdea3ba0169f65564b9a081a1b3fcf035d9ef5448", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1622 bytes to tests/src/io.lettuce/lettuce-core/6.2.6.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_lettuce/lettuce_core/ReflectionUtilsTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777751399334}]}
